1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,000
[English subtitles are available]

2
00:01:32,280 --> 00:01:40,640
[You are My Fateful Love]
[EP24]

3
00:01:49,359 --> 00:01:50,040
It's me.

4
00:02:13,479 --> 00:02:13,879
Sorry...
Xu Huaisong.

5
00:02:17,879 --> 00:02:19,800
Let's get to know each other again.

6
00:02:22,759 --> 00:02:23,879
This time,

7
00:02:26,280 --> 00:02:27,520
with our truest,

8
00:02:30,479 --> 00:02:31,520
most honest selves.

9
00:02:45,520 --> 00:02:46,240
Hi.

10
00:02:49,240 --> 00:02:50,400
I'm Ruan Yu,

11
00:02:52,080 --> 00:02:53,400
from Su City No.1 High School,

12
00:02:54,360 --> 00:02:55,960
Class 9, Senior Year.

13
00:03:01,240 --> 00:03:02,639
I used to really like you.

14
00:03:05,159 --> 00:03:05,879
And now...
Wait.

15
00:03:09,800 --> 00:03:10,439
That line...

16
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:13,039
should be mine first.

17
00:03:22,120 --> 00:03:22,719
Hi.

18
00:03:25,159 --> 00:03:26,879
I'm Xu Huaisong from Su City No.1 High School,

19
00:03:28,319 --> 00:03:29,840
Class 10, Senior Year.

20
00:03:33,199 --> 00:03:34,479
I liked you very much back then.

21
00:03:36,439 --> 00:03:37,120
And now,

22
00:03:40,759 --> 00:03:42,080
I like you even more.

23
00:03:53,879 --> 00:03:54,520
So...

24
00:03:56,319 --> 00:03:57,439
a handshaking or not?

25
00:03:58,960 --> 00:03:59,759
If not, then...

26
00:04:12,759 --> 00:04:13,599
hug me instead.

27
00:04:58,639 --> 00:04:59,480
[Sorry about that.]

28
00:04:59,800 --> 00:05:01,439
[I was on patrol here,]

29
00:05:01,439 --> 00:05:02,879
[then saw you two doing this...]

30
00:05:03,360 --> 00:05:04,759
[It felt like a movie scene.]

31
00:05:05,240 --> 00:05:06,079
[I got sucked right in.]

32
00:05:06,480 --> 00:05:07,560
Sorry to interrupt, sorry.

33
00:05:07,639 --> 00:05:08,800
Um, I'm leaving now.

34
00:05:09,160 --> 00:05:09,879
I'm leaving now.

35
00:05:10,120 --> 00:05:12,079
We were just rehearsing a movie script.

36
00:05:12,519 --> 00:05:13,800
We just finished one scene.

37
00:05:13,800 --> 00:05:14,519
We're going inside now

38
00:05:14,600 --> 00:05:15,560
to work out the details.

39
00:05:35,120 --> 00:05:36,439
What details are you working out?

40
00:05:48,439 --> 00:05:48,920
There is

41
00:05:48,920 --> 00:05:50,199
one detail I can't figure out.

42
00:06:12,040 --> 00:06:13,079
I'm really curious.

43
00:06:14,120 --> 00:06:15,839
Before it saw daylight again,

44
00:06:17,040 --> 00:06:18,279
how did it survive

45
00:06:18,279 --> 00:06:19,160
all these years intact?

46
00:06:21,720 --> 00:06:22,680
When I left back then,

47
00:06:22,680 --> 00:06:23,879
I took the battery out,

48
00:06:24,600 --> 00:06:25,759
and sealed the phone and battery

49
00:06:26,160 --> 00:06:27,399
inside an airtight box.

50
00:06:29,279 --> 00:06:30,040
Of course,

51
00:06:31,600 --> 00:06:32,360
you could also ask

52
00:06:32,360 --> 00:06:33,480
the phone manufacturer

53
00:06:34,199 --> 00:06:35,480
how they managed to create

54
00:06:35,480 --> 00:06:36,519
this miracle.

55
00:06:42,600 --> 00:06:43,560
Then you...

56
00:06:47,160 --> 00:06:48,399
stood there so long.

57
00:06:51,199 --> 00:06:52,040
Aren't you hungry?

58
00:06:59,560 --> 00:07:00,720
I ate on the plane.

59
00:07:05,639 --> 00:07:06,920
Ate on the plane?

60
00:07:14,120 --> 00:07:15,680
What a pity, then.

61
00:07:16,759 --> 00:07:19,319
The midnight snack I prepared...

62
00:07:20,920 --> 00:07:21,720
you're not having it?

63
00:07:24,560 --> 00:07:26,399
Make it. I'm suddenly hungry again.

64
00:07:38,360 --> 00:07:39,039
Cheers.
Cheers.

65
00:07:43,920 --> 00:07:44,680
Have some Coke.

66
00:07:45,560 --> 00:07:46,560
It really tastes great.

67
00:07:49,240 --> 00:07:50,439
All that fried chicken you ate as a kid

68
00:07:50,439 --> 00:07:51,079
paid off.

69
00:08:03,360 --> 00:08:04,600
One last question.

70
00:08:06,040 --> 00:08:07,560
At the very start,

71
00:08:08,480 --> 00:08:09,959
how did you notice me?

72
00:08:18,839 --> 00:08:19,399
Boss,

73
00:08:19,519 --> 00:08:20,480
has Issue Three of Galactic Empire
arrived yet?

74
00:08:21,720 --> 00:08:23,160
Miss, you're late.

75
00:08:23,680 --> 00:08:24,319
There was only one.
It was just borrowed.

76
00:08:26,639 --> 00:08:27,759
The handsome guy in there took it.

77
00:08:29,439 --> 00:08:30,439
Judging by his uniform,

78
00:08:30,680 --> 00:08:32,080
he seems to be from your school too.

79
00:08:33,559 --> 00:08:34,120
Maybe

80
00:08:34,480 --> 00:08:35,440
you can ask him about it.

81
00:08:37,120 --> 00:08:38,240
Though he looks like he's asleep.

82
00:08:42,200 --> 00:08:43,159
Forget it.

83
00:08:44,039 --> 00:08:45,159
I'll wait till he's done

84
00:08:45,320 --> 00:08:45,879
reading it.

85
00:08:46,480 --> 00:08:47,120
That works too.

86
00:08:50,159 --> 00:08:52,080
On such a beautiful weekend afternoon,

87
00:08:52,799 --> 00:08:53,559
getting to nap

88
00:08:53,559 --> 00:08:55,120
with your favorite comic beside,

89
00:08:55,879 --> 00:08:56,960
that's pure bliss.

90
00:08:57,360 --> 00:08:58,159
Life, you know,

91
00:08:59,600 --> 00:09:00,879
should be lived again and again

92
00:09:01,200 --> 00:09:02,600
in wonderful moments like this.

93
00:09:06,200 --> 00:09:07,679
You're our head teacher's daughter.

94
00:09:08,519 --> 00:09:09,799
Everyone in our class

95
00:09:10,080 --> 00:09:10,799
knew who you were.

96
00:09:11,360 --> 00:09:12,320
That's all?

97
00:09:13,480 --> 00:09:14,120
No...

98
00:09:14,919 --> 00:09:15,679
No romantic

99
00:09:15,720 --> 00:09:16,960
meet- cute

100
00:09:17,759 --> 00:09:18,679
like in love stories?

101
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:19,960
So if there wasn't one,

102
00:09:20,279 --> 00:09:21,679
I can't be your male lead?

103
00:09:23,840 --> 00:09:24,840
You can, you can.

104
00:09:25,200 --> 00:09:26,960
I'll let you be it all you want.

105
00:09:29,559 --> 00:09:31,399
I've already been the male lead for many chapters.

106
00:09:33,200 --> 00:09:33,960
Maybe stop now.

107
00:09:34,519 --> 00:09:35,600
What do you mean?

108
00:09:38,279 --> 00:09:39,679
So can we

109
00:09:40,320 --> 00:09:41,960
officially upgrade my status now?

110
00:09:53,519 --> 00:09:54,279
Pipi,

111
00:09:54,519 --> 00:09:55,960
why are you so naughty?

112
00:09:56,240 --> 00:09:57,320
Don't you know your sister is talking

113
00:09:57,320 --> 00:09:58,399
about something important?

114
00:09:58,399 --> 00:09:59,519
Come on, listen together.

115
00:10:01,679 --> 00:10:02,320
Together.

116
00:10:04,080 --> 00:10:04,720
What's wrong?
What are you sniffing?

117
00:10:07,600 --> 00:10:08,480
Sniffing what?

118
00:10:09,039 --> 00:10:10,759
The cooking smell on us, of course.

119
00:10:14,440 --> 00:10:15,320
I've got

120
00:10:16,360 --> 00:10:17,399
cooking smell on me too.

121
00:10:17,559 --> 00:10:18,720
I picked it up from your place.

122
00:10:19,639 --> 00:10:20,759
Is it your responsibility?

123
00:10:22,440 --> 00:10:23,919
How...How to take?

124
00:10:27,639 --> 00:10:28,679
Let me take a shower.

125
00:10:30,720 --> 00:10:31,519
[A shower?]

126
00:10:32,480 --> 00:10:33,960
[We were just upgrading status.]

127
00:10:34,879 --> 00:10:35,759
[So fast?]

128
00:10:41,759 --> 00:10:42,480
You...

129
00:10:42,879 --> 00:10:43,679
you didn't even bring

130
00:10:43,679 --> 00:10:44,759
a change of clothes.

131
00:10:45,120 --> 00:10:46,240
After your shower,

132
00:10:46,519 --> 00:10:47,480
what are you gonna wear?

133
00:10:47,600 --> 00:10:48,320
I brought some.

134
00:10:53,440 --> 00:10:54,159
In the car downstairs..

135
00:11:00,519 --> 00:11:01,480
So tonight...

136
00:11:03,080 --> 00:11:04,440
are you staying over?

137
00:11:05,720 --> 00:11:06,679
What are you thinking?

138
00:11:08,720 --> 00:11:09,720
I mean,

139
00:11:09,879 --> 00:11:11,080
if you're staying,

140
00:11:11,320 --> 00:11:12,200
I'll get the guest room
ready for you.

141
00:11:13,360 --> 00:11:14,039
No need.

142
00:11:16,279 --> 00:11:18,120
I'll stay, but not sleep over.

143
00:11:19,200 --> 00:11:20,440
I'm still jet- lagged.

144
00:11:20,720 --> 00:11:22,159
I'll work in the living room later

145
00:11:22,279 --> 00:11:23,039
and stay with you.

146
00:11:24,000 --> 00:11:24,639
Then you probably
won't have nightmares.

147
00:11:30,159 --> 00:11:31,120
I'll get my things later.

148
00:11:31,919 --> 00:11:32,720
You get ready first.

149
00:11:33,080 --> 00:11:33,840
Go to bed early.

150
00:11:37,200 --> 00:11:37,720
Go on.

151
00:11:42,559 --> 00:11:43,200
Good night.

152
00:11:43,600 --> 00:11:44,279
Good night.

153
00:11:46,600 --> 00:11:47,320
Boyfriend.

154
00:11:51,960 --> 00:11:52,879
Boyfriend?

155
00:12:00,039 --> 00:12:01,519
Boyfriend!

156
00:12:17,519 --> 00:12:18,559
[Did I say]

157
00:12:18,840 --> 00:12:20,080
["good night" too early?]

158
00:12:24,720 --> 00:12:25,639
[Before bed,]

159
00:12:26,200 --> 00:12:27,200
[aren't we really]

160
00:12:27,600 --> 00:12:28,720
[doing anything else?]

161
00:12:42,320 --> 00:12:44,720
Xu Huaisong is at my place tonight.

162
00:12:51,200 --> 00:12:52,559
So you two finally dropped the act

163
00:12:52,559 --> 00:12:54,279
and are getting honest now?

164
00:12:55,600 --> 00:12:56,279
I'm lying

165
00:12:56,279 --> 00:12:57,679
on my bed right now.

166
00:12:59,639 --> 00:13:00,519
Secretly thrilled?

167
00:13:02,480 --> 00:13:04,159
Tossing and turning.

168
00:13:05,200 --> 00:13:06,159
Nervous?

169
00:13:09,080 --> 00:13:10,480
He's in the living room now.

170
00:13:11,919 --> 00:13:13,279
Getting ready?

171
00:13:17,080 --> 00:13:18,559
No, he's busy working.

172
00:13:22,000 --> 00:13:23,360
You both like each other,

173
00:13:23,600 --> 00:13:25,240
a man and a woman,

174
00:13:25,399 --> 00:13:26,440
alone in one room,

175
00:13:26,440 --> 00:13:27,480
and he's still working?

176
00:13:28,679 --> 00:13:29,799
Don't tell me he...

177
00:13:32,200 --> 00:13:32,960
What?

178
00:13:33,720 --> 00:13:34,639
He can't?

179
00:13:46,840 --> 00:13:48,000
[Why did you suddenly come back?]

180
00:13:48,279 --> 00:13:49,120
[Was it urgent?]

181
00:13:52,120 --> 00:13:53,200
Coming back to be a boyfriend,

182
00:13:53,679 --> 00:13:54,519
is it urgent?

183
00:13:56,639 --> 00:13:57,799
[The official kind?]

184
00:13:59,519 --> 00:14:00,240
What else?

185
00:14:01,120 --> 00:14:01,960
[No probation period?]

186
00:14:04,799 --> 00:14:06,000
It's not a job interview.

187
00:14:06,320 --> 00:14:07,519
Why is there a probation period?

188
00:14:15,240 --> 00:14:15,960
[Alright.]
[So...]

189
00:14:16,879 --> 00:14:18,519
[So you are now...]

190
00:14:21,080 --> 00:14:22,799
Working at her home.

191
00:14:24,960 --> 00:14:26,159
[You, as a boyfriend,]

192
00:14:26,159 --> 00:14:27,120
[isn't just official.]

193
00:14:27,679 --> 00:14:29,320
[You're upright to a scary degree.]

194
00:14:35,519 --> 00:14:37,440
Too ... upright?

195
00:14:38,399 --> 00:14:39,159
Too upright.

196
00:14:39,159 --> 00:14:40,600
Seriously too upright.

197
00:14:40,600 --> 00:14:42,320
Upright to a scary degree.

198
00:14:42,519 --> 00:14:43,639
Give him an award.

199
00:14:46,440 --> 00:14:47,480
If he's that proper,

200
00:14:48,279 --> 00:14:50,440
I have to be a little improper.

201
00:15:13,360 --> 00:15:14,120
Ruan Yu?

202
00:15:21,720 --> 00:15:22,399
What is it?

203
00:15:23,799 --> 00:15:24,200
It's so late.

204
00:15:24,200 --> 00:15:25,399
Why are you still scrolling videos?

205
00:15:30,000 --> 00:15:31,360
I can't really sleep.

206
00:15:32,080 --> 00:15:33,279
I'm kinda bored.

207
00:15:35,759 --> 00:15:36,679
Then I'm coming in.

208
00:15:54,720 --> 00:15:55,639
I thought

209
00:15:56,279 --> 00:15:57,519
you should get to sleep early.

210
00:15:58,519 --> 00:15:59,840
I was bored in the living room alone.

211
00:16:00,639 --> 00:16:01,679
Why are you bored too?

212
00:16:04,240 --> 00:16:05,360
So you're bored, huh?

213
00:16:06,679 --> 00:16:07,480
Then how about

214
00:16:08,399 --> 00:16:09,480
I chat a little with you?

215
00:16:38,879 --> 00:16:40,360
I said I'd chat with you.

216
00:16:41,320 --> 00:16:42,279
Why are you laughing?

217
00:16:44,159 --> 00:16:46,080
Am I? Was I laughing?

218
00:16:47,200 --> 00:16:47,960
You were.

219
00:16:48,799 --> 00:16:49,759
What are you laughing at?

220
00:16:51,519 --> 00:16:52,519
I'm laughing

221
00:16:53,440 --> 00:16:54,399
at how my girlfriend

222
00:16:54,399 --> 00:16:55,799
tricked me into her room.

223
00:17:03,200 --> 00:17:04,319
Didn't you ask?

224
00:17:08,480 --> 00:17:09,319
I don't want to ask now.

225
00:17:09,519 --> 00:17:10,400
So annoying.

226
00:17:10,640 --> 00:17:11,359
Get out.

227
00:17:14,160 --> 00:17:14,960
Are you angry?

228
00:17:15,440 --> 00:17:16,319
I'm not angry.

229
00:17:19,759 --> 00:17:20,480
Alright, alright.

230
00:17:21,640 --> 00:17:22,640
I myself wanted to come in.

231
00:17:26,000 --> 00:17:26,839
Come out first.
Don't hide in there.

232
00:17:27,880 --> 00:17:28,680
You won't sleep well.

233
00:17:29,559 --> 00:17:30,440
What are you doing?

234
00:17:36,119 --> 00:17:37,720
All those 300 texts of mine,

235
00:17:38,039 --> 00:17:39,000
all those little tricks,

236
00:17:39,200 --> 00:17:40,240
you saw all of them.

237
00:17:40,759 --> 00:17:41,759
I didn't say anything, right?

238
00:17:44,319 --> 00:17:45,720
That was payback.

239
00:17:47,359 --> 00:17:48,160
That's on you.

240
00:17:48,160 --> 00:17:49,759
You were way too smug reading my novel.

241
00:17:50,079 --> 00:17:50,839
You even made me read it.

242
00:17:59,400 --> 00:18:00,599
What did I make you read?

243
00:18:05,279 --> 00:18:07,240
Nothing. I'm gonna sleep.

244
00:18:14,160 --> 00:18:15,160
Explain before sleep.

245
00:18:23,480 --> 00:18:24,160
Fine.

246
00:18:27,240 --> 00:18:29,279
Let me state this very seriously.

247
00:18:30,279 --> 00:18:31,200
Everything

248
00:18:31,200 --> 00:18:33,200
in Chapter 23 of my novel

249
00:18:33,519 --> 00:18:34,920
was purely made up

250
00:18:35,200 --> 00:18:36,839
for dramatic effect.

251
00:18:38,759 --> 00:18:39,440
I...

252
00:18:40,880 --> 00:18:42,559
I personally never,

253
00:18:44,400 --> 00:18:45,920
absolutely never did any of

254
00:18:48,480 --> 00:18:49,240
those things.

255
00:18:52,359 --> 00:18:53,160
Still,

256
00:18:54,400 --> 00:18:55,319
it was well written.

257
00:18:58,160 --> 00:18:58,839
Really?

258
00:19:00,119 --> 00:19:01,559
Never been in love once,

259
00:19:02,880 --> 00:19:03,799
yet you wrote

260
00:19:04,359 --> 00:19:06,039
the kissing scene pretty realistically.

261
00:19:06,640 --> 00:19:07,440
Of course.

262
00:19:08,000 --> 00:19:08,920
I may not know it firsthand,
but I get the idea.

263
00:19:22,039 --> 00:19:22,920
What are you doing?

264
00:19:28,039 --> 00:19:29,240
Then let me show you.

265
00:20:29,680 --> 00:20:31,440
[How is he so calm?]

266
00:20:47,279 --> 00:20:48,200
You can't tell

267
00:20:49,160 --> 00:20:50,279
from my face.

268
00:20:52,920 --> 00:20:53,640
You have to listen.

269
00:20:57,279 --> 00:20:58,480
It's even louder

270
00:20:59,200 --> 00:21:00,000
than fireworks.

271
00:21:28,440 --> 00:21:29,039
Coming!

272
00:21:47,240 --> 00:21:48,079
Wrong place?

273
00:21:51,839 --> 00:21:52,799
What are you saying?

274
00:21:53,119 --> 00:21:54,240
Isn't Xu here?

275
00:21:54,480 --> 00:21:55,519
We're not at the wrong place.

276
00:22:00,400 --> 00:22:01,680
Mr. Ruan, Ms. Qu, please come in.

277
00:22:02,240 --> 00:22:02,799
Come in.

278
00:22:05,160 --> 00:22:05,960
I'll get the slippers.

279
00:22:07,359 --> 00:22:08,400
The pink pair is mine.

280
00:22:08,759 --> 00:22:09,440
Okay, okay.

281
00:22:10,000 --> 00:22:10,599
Okay, thanks.

282
00:22:10,680 --> 00:22:11,720
Thanks, thanks, thanks.

283
00:22:14,720 --> 00:22:15,319
Here.

284
00:22:19,160 --> 00:22:20,079
I made steamed buns.

285
00:22:22,440 --> 00:22:23,200
I cooked some porridge.

286
00:22:28,799 --> 00:22:29,960
Sit and change shoes.

287
00:22:34,119 --> 00:22:34,680
What?

288
00:22:35,559 --> 00:22:37,200
You'd rather think it's the wrong door

289
00:22:37,680 --> 00:22:38,519
than believe your daughter
is really dating?

290
00:22:39,440 --> 00:22:40,079
It's not that.

291
00:22:40,759 --> 00:22:41,599
No dating till now,

292
00:22:41,599 --> 00:22:43,119
and now this fast?

293
00:22:44,119 --> 00:22:45,720
Don't jump to conclusions so quickly.

294
00:22:46,519 --> 00:22:47,640
Let's see what's going on first.

295
00:22:48,640 --> 00:22:49,480
Shoes, shoes, shoes.

296
00:22:52,759 --> 00:22:53,400
Xu.

297
00:22:55,039 --> 00:22:55,680
Where is Yu?

298
00:22:56,359 --> 00:22:58,519
She's still asleep.

299
00:23:03,440 --> 00:23:04,480
Still asleep?

300
00:23:05,039 --> 00:23:05,720
She's usually not
one to sleep in.

301
00:23:06,599 --> 00:23:07,799
Why isn't she up yet?

302
00:23:10,240 --> 00:23:10,920
Maybe

303
00:23:11,400 --> 00:23:12,279
you should go wake her.
Okay.

304
00:23:21,880 --> 00:23:23,039
It's not really convenient.

305
00:23:23,759 --> 00:23:24,720
Maybe Ms. Qu,

306
00:23:24,799 --> 00:23:25,680
you should go instead.

307
00:23:31,000 --> 00:23:31,680
Right, right, right.
I'll wake her.

308
00:23:33,559 --> 00:23:34,359
She's my daughter after all.

309
00:23:35,759 --> 00:23:36,400
Here, hold this.

310
00:23:53,680 --> 00:23:54,319
You go ahead.

311
00:24:02,599 --> 00:24:03,680
Sleeping that soundly.

312
00:24:10,799 --> 00:24:11,599
Yu.

313
00:24:12,799 --> 00:24:13,839
Xu Huaisong.

314
00:24:14,839 --> 00:24:15,759
What time is it?

315
00:24:19,119 --> 00:24:20,079
I'm your mother.

316
00:24:21,680 --> 00:24:22,400
Mom.

317
00:24:24,680 --> 00:24:25,279
Mom?

318
00:24:25,880 --> 00:24:26,400
Mom!

319
00:24:28,240 --> 00:24:29,480
Why ... Why are you here, Mom?

320
00:24:29,720 --> 00:24:30,319
What?

321
00:24:30,960 --> 00:24:32,160
Am I here at a bad time?

322
00:24:34,400 --> 00:24:36,440
No. No, no.

323
00:24:38,440 --> 00:24:39,079
Hurry up.
Get up and wash up.

324
00:24:40,160 --> 00:24:40,799
Come and have breakfast.
Your dad's here too.

325
00:24:42,000 --> 00:24:42,319
Hurry.

326
00:24:44,359 --> 00:24:45,000
Hurry up.

327
00:24:47,000 --> 00:24:47,640
My dad?

328
00:25:01,599 --> 00:25:02,279
Xu,

329
00:25:03,960 --> 00:25:04,799
you just

330
00:25:05,079 --> 00:25:06,160
got back from overseas?

331
00:25:06,720 --> 00:25:08,480
Yes. I got back last night.

332
00:25:08,680 --> 00:25:09,599
I'm still jet- lagged,

333
00:25:09,880 --> 00:25:10,839
so I worked all night.

334
00:25:13,440 --> 00:25:14,480
It's good for the young to stay busy.

335
00:25:14,759 --> 00:25:15,960
Right, right, right.

336
00:25:16,160 --> 00:25:17,319
So this time back,

337
00:25:17,559 --> 00:25:18,880
are you all done with things over there?

338
00:25:19,079 --> 00:25:19,599
Not yet.

339
00:25:20,039 --> 00:25:21,359
A few cases still need wrapping up.

340
00:25:21,559 --> 00:25:23,079
I'll have to go back again later.

341
00:25:30,079 --> 00:25:30,960
But...

342
00:25:31,720 --> 00:25:32,480
I've already stopped
taking on new cases.

343
00:25:38,319 --> 00:25:39,240
Xu,

344
00:25:39,640 --> 00:25:41,000
so your plan is?

345
00:25:43,640 --> 00:25:44,720
I'll come back and build career here.

346
00:25:46,440 --> 00:25:47,359
Good, good.

347
00:25:49,400 --> 00:25:50,000
Where's Yu?
Still not done yet?

348
00:25:51,200 --> 00:25:51,880
Yu!

349
00:25:52,640 --> 00:25:53,720
Why are you dawdling?

350
00:25:53,880 --> 00:25:55,079
Come out and have breakfast.

351
00:25:55,559 --> 00:25:56,200
Coming, Mom!

352
00:25:57,839 --> 00:25:58,759
Come eat breakfast.

353
00:25:59,319 --> 00:25:59,880
Come!

354
00:26:02,240 --> 00:26:02,920
Look.

355
00:26:03,319 --> 00:26:04,440
Your dad made these buns for you.

356
00:26:04,640 --> 00:26:05,640
He's been busy all morning.

357
00:26:06,160 --> 00:26:06,920
There are veggie buns
and meat buns too.

358
00:26:07,559 --> 00:26:08,200
Right?

359
00:26:09,240 --> 00:26:10,839
All my favorites. Thanks, Dad.

360
00:26:11,359 --> 00:26:12,400
And Xu

361
00:26:12,759 --> 00:26:14,000
made porridge for you.

362
00:26:23,839 --> 00:26:24,400
Mom, Dad,

363
00:26:24,960 --> 00:26:25,440
why did you two
come so early today?

364
00:26:27,279 --> 00:26:28,480
We were worried you weren't sleeping well.

365
00:26:29,000 --> 00:26:29,799
Last time at home,
the huge dark circles

366
00:26:30,319 --> 00:26:31,440
under your eyes

367
00:26:32,079 --> 00:26:33,359
nearly look like a panda.

368
00:26:33,359 --> 00:26:34,039
Right?

369
00:26:35,559 --> 00:26:37,240
Well, now,

370
00:26:37,240 --> 00:26:38,400
we don't have to worry so much.

371
00:26:38,400 --> 00:26:39,079
Thanks.

372
00:26:45,119 --> 00:26:45,720
Xu,

373
00:26:46,440 --> 00:26:47,359
do you know
what's going on

374
00:26:48,000 --> 00:26:48,920
with Zhou Jun now?

375
00:26:50,160 --> 00:26:51,720
The police have currently taken

376
00:26:51,720 --> 00:26:52,599
coercive measures.

377
00:26:53,279 --> 00:26:54,119
As for the details,

378
00:26:54,319 --> 00:26:55,400
I won't know

379
00:26:55,400 --> 00:26:56,200
until after the meeting.

380
00:26:56,599 --> 00:26:57,559
I was thinking of
going to the firm later

381
00:26:58,480 --> 00:26:59,480
to learn more about it.

382
00:27:00,480 --> 00:27:01,079
Okay.

383
00:27:02,559 --> 00:27:03,200
After breakfast,
I'll go with you.

384
00:27:09,119 --> 00:27:10,519
Have one of Dad's buns.

385
00:27:10,519 --> 00:27:11,440
Eat, eat, eat.

386
00:27:19,000 --> 00:27:19,640
Get in.

387
00:27:24,640 --> 00:27:25,400
Xu,

388
00:27:25,960 --> 00:27:27,400
so your plan is?

389
00:27:29,319 --> 00:27:30,519
I'll come back and build career here.

390
00:27:36,480 --> 00:27:37,119
Wait.

391
00:27:40,519 --> 00:27:41,160
What's wrong?

392
00:27:44,759 --> 00:27:46,279
When I was brushing my teeth,

393
00:27:46,799 --> 00:27:48,640
I heard what you told my parents.

394
00:27:52,880 --> 00:27:54,000
Actually,

395
00:27:54,359 --> 00:27:54,920
I planned to

396
00:27:54,920 --> 00:27:56,119
tell you in a few days.

397
00:27:56,960 --> 00:27:58,400
But your parents

398
00:27:58,599 --> 00:27:59,960
seemed a little uneasy,

399
00:28:00,640 --> 00:28:01,200
so I made

400
00:28:01,200 --> 00:28:02,279
my position clear early.

401
00:28:03,640 --> 00:28:04,519
This is such a big deal.
How could you just

402
00:28:05,359 --> 00:28:06,319
decide like that?

403
00:28:06,960 --> 00:28:07,960
The career you built over there

404
00:28:07,960 --> 00:28:09,200
all these years,

405
00:28:09,400 --> 00:28:11,079
and the network and resources you've built...

406
00:28:11,759 --> 00:28:12,960
None of them matters more than you.

407
00:28:16,720 --> 00:28:17,680
But I still hope
we solve this

408
00:28:18,400 --> 00:28:19,599
together.

409
00:28:20,319 --> 00:28:21,359
Actually, these days,

410
00:28:21,640 --> 00:28:23,160
I've been thinking about this too.

411
00:28:23,839 --> 00:28:25,440
I meant to tell you in person.

412
00:28:26,359 --> 00:28:27,000
Look,

413
00:28:27,799 --> 00:28:29,079
the nature of my work

414
00:28:29,200 --> 00:28:30,559
isn't very tied to one location.

415
00:28:30,960 --> 00:28:31,400
I don't need

416
00:28:31,400 --> 00:28:32,480
to stay in China

417
00:28:32,480 --> 00:28:33,279
all 365 days a year.

418
00:28:33,839 --> 00:28:34,640
Maybe in the future,

419
00:28:34,960 --> 00:28:36,480
I can spend part of my time

420
00:28:36,519 --> 00:28:37,559
living abroad for a while.

421
00:28:37,960 --> 00:28:39,039
You wouldn't have to completely give up

422
00:28:39,039 --> 00:28:39,799
your career there.

423
00:28:40,119 --> 00:28:41,200
You could develop

424
00:28:41,400 --> 00:28:42,839
both domestic and overseas business.

425
00:28:44,480 --> 00:28:45,079
That way,
every year

426
00:28:45,880 --> 00:28:46,559
you'd also have some time
to stay here in China.

427
00:28:48,279 --> 00:28:49,759
Don't you think

428
00:28:49,759 --> 00:28:50,960
that would be a more balanced solution?

429
00:28:52,519 --> 00:28:53,440
You're right.

430
00:28:55,000 --> 00:28:56,000
But do you want

431
00:28:56,400 --> 00:28:57,519
to hear mine?

432
00:29:00,240 --> 00:29:00,880
Do you know why

433
00:29:00,880 --> 00:29:02,480
I never changed my nationality?

434
00:29:04,680 --> 00:29:05,240
Why?

435
00:29:05,559 --> 00:29:06,599
Because to me,

436
00:29:07,759 --> 00:29:08,440
that place

437
00:29:08,799 --> 00:29:10,160
was never truly home.

438
00:29:11,279 --> 00:29:12,359
My roots are in China.

439
00:29:12,880 --> 00:29:13,960
My family is in China.

440
00:29:14,359 --> 00:29:15,400
And now you.

441
00:29:16,000 --> 00:29:17,039
You're waiting for me too.

442
00:29:17,920 --> 00:29:19,160
So I have to come back.

443
00:29:22,720 --> 00:29:23,599
What about Uncle, then?

444
00:29:24,039 --> 00:29:25,079
What about him being overseas

445
00:29:25,079 --> 00:29:25,720
alone?

446
00:29:26,799 --> 00:29:28,319
Actually, before Dad got sick,

447
00:29:28,559 --> 00:29:29,680
he never once brought up

448
00:29:29,680 --> 00:29:30,839
changing nationality.

449
00:29:31,559 --> 00:29:32,119
I used to think

450
00:29:32,119 --> 00:29:33,480
maybe he had other plans.

451
00:29:33,799 --> 00:29:34,920
But after he got sick,

452
00:29:34,920 --> 00:29:36,519
I sorted through his work materials.

453
00:29:37,039 --> 00:29:38,519
I found out he had always

454
00:29:38,519 --> 00:29:39,440
been investing in China.

455
00:29:40,880 --> 00:29:43,160
Before he went into the ER this time,

456
00:29:43,640 --> 00:29:45,119
he was still clutching our family photo.

457
00:29:46,680 --> 00:29:48,079
I think maybe Dad regretted it.

458
00:29:50,200 --> 00:29:51,319
But right now,

459
00:29:51,759 --> 00:29:53,119
his still needs time to recover.

460
00:29:54,000 --> 00:29:54,960
Bringing him back to China

461
00:29:55,400 --> 00:29:56,039
will have to wait.

462
00:30:01,799 --> 00:30:02,920
Actually, I'm really happy

463
00:30:03,480 --> 00:30:04,319
you're willing to

464
00:30:04,319 --> 00:30:05,480
think about this for me.

465
00:30:07,240 --> 00:30:08,240
But the most important thing

466
00:30:09,319 --> 00:30:10,720
I've built up over these years

467
00:30:11,079 --> 00:30:12,359
isn't contacts or resources that become useless

468
00:30:12,359 --> 00:30:13,759
in another place.

469
00:30:14,400 --> 00:30:15,119
It's ability.

470
00:30:16,039 --> 00:30:17,200
If I have the ability

471
00:30:17,200 --> 00:30:18,319
to be a good lawyer abroad,

472
00:30:19,000 --> 00:30:21,039
then I can do it here in China too.

473
00:30:21,440 --> 00:30:23,000
The past ten years may feel long,

474
00:30:23,200 --> 00:30:24,079
but compared with

475
00:30:24,079 --> 00:30:25,240
the decades ahead,

476
00:30:25,920 --> 00:30:27,119
aren't they hardly worth mentioning?

477
00:30:31,359 --> 00:30:32,519
Seat belt on. Let's go.

478
00:30:43,880 --> 00:30:44,920
This time, she really found

479
00:30:44,920 --> 00:30:46,039
a lawyer boyfriend.

480
00:30:46,480 --> 00:30:47,640
You can relax now, right?

481
00:30:50,039 --> 00:30:51,079
In her line of work,

482
00:30:51,599 --> 00:30:53,079
it looks pretty simple, socially.

483
00:30:53,680 --> 00:30:54,599
Fewer people to deal with,
hardly goes out.

484
00:30:56,640 --> 00:30:57,599
But you know

485
00:30:58,519 --> 00:30:59,920
how awful all that online talk

486
00:31:00,319 --> 00:31:01,480
can be.

487
00:31:03,799 --> 00:31:04,960
We literature people

488
00:31:05,200 --> 00:31:06,240
feel things deeply.

489
00:31:06,880 --> 00:31:07,799
Some words

490
00:31:08,319 --> 00:31:09,480
really get under your skin.

491
00:31:10,400 --> 00:31:11,359
So I thought,
find her a lawyer,

492
00:31:12,480 --> 00:31:13,640
someone who can help anytime.

493
00:31:15,000 --> 00:31:15,599
That's why

494
00:31:15,599 --> 00:31:17,200
I introduced her to so many lawyers.

495
00:31:17,839 --> 00:31:20,240
I mean, while we're still alive,

496
00:31:20,640 --> 00:31:21,519
if something happens to her,

497
00:31:21,519 --> 00:31:22,559
we can be there for her.

498
00:31:25,559 --> 00:31:27,519
But if someday we're gone,

499
00:31:28,359 --> 00:31:29,559
and she's all alone,

500
00:31:30,119 --> 00:31:31,559
how could I not worry?

501
00:31:35,119 --> 00:31:36,960
Seeing Xu here today, right,

502
00:31:38,079 --> 00:31:39,960
and hearing he plans to come back to work,

503
00:31:41,720 --> 00:31:42,839
I feel much more at ease.

504
00:31:44,240 --> 00:31:45,480
Don't say things like that.

505
00:31:45,960 --> 00:31:47,240
Look at you now.

506
00:31:47,880 --> 00:31:48,599
Three meals a day,

507
00:31:48,599 --> 00:31:49,880
two big bowls each meal,

508
00:31:50,000 --> 00:31:51,039
eating well, sleeping well.

509
00:31:51,119 --> 00:31:52,200
Don't think about things like that.

510
00:31:52,200 --> 00:31:53,400
Oh, come on.

511
00:31:53,400 --> 00:31:54,440
I really can't talk to you

512
00:31:54,440 --> 00:31:55,880
science guys.

513
00:31:56,920 --> 00:31:58,640
This means I'm healthy, right?

514
00:31:59,720 --> 00:32:01,480
I'm just planning ahead.

515
00:32:02,519 --> 00:32:04,880
Or maybe worrying too much.

516
00:32:06,400 --> 00:32:07,160
Nice idiom,

517
00:32:07,160 --> 00:32:08,319
wrong time to use it.

518
00:32:08,599 --> 00:32:09,240
Right now, you'd better
heat up this bun

519
00:32:09,799 --> 00:32:10,519
for me.

520
00:32:10,519 --> 00:32:11,720
I was too busy watching them just now,

521
00:32:11,720 --> 00:32:12,279
I didn't even eat properly.

522
00:32:12,279 --> 00:32:13,319
I'm still hungry.

523
00:32:13,720 --> 00:32:15,240
I'll make you fresh ones.

524
00:32:15,240 --> 00:32:15,799
Fresh ones?

525
00:32:15,799 --> 00:32:17,400
Does your daughter even have flour here?

526
00:32:17,400 --> 00:32:18,240
Fresh ones.

527
00:32:27,799 --> 00:32:29,400
Am I seeing things wrong?

528
00:32:31,920 --> 00:32:33,200
Do I need to get my eyes

529
00:32:33,519 --> 00:32:34,240
checked?

530
00:32:34,640 --> 00:32:35,359
No, no, no.

531
00:32:36,119 --> 00:32:37,279
If you're going to hospital,

532
00:32:37,880 --> 00:32:39,000
I'd recommend neurology more.

533
00:32:39,799 --> 00:32:40,759
See if they can

534
00:32:40,880 --> 00:32:42,279
prescribe something for slow reaction time.

535
00:32:43,039 --> 00:32:43,559
What do you mean?

536
00:32:43,559 --> 00:32:44,720
I'm not the last person

537
00:32:44,720 --> 00:32:45,200
in the company

538
00:32:45,200 --> 00:32:46,240
to know this, am I?

539
00:32:48,559 --> 00:32:49,720
You can ask the cleaning lady.

540
00:32:52,000 --> 00:32:53,440
If she still doesn't know,

541
00:32:54,039 --> 00:32:55,200
then you're second to last.

542
00:33:05,079 --> 00:33:05,880
You're here early.

543
00:33:07,000 --> 00:33:08,599
[Full- time staff really are different.]

544
00:33:08,880 --> 00:33:10,480
[So open about it after being official.]

545
00:33:10,799 --> 00:33:11,960
[Unlike me, a temp worker.]

546
00:33:11,960 --> 00:33:12,960
[Stuck in a secret relationship.]

547
00:33:17,440 --> 00:33:18,200
What are you looking at?

548
00:33:22,880 --> 00:33:24,359
Your happiness

549
00:33:24,720 --> 00:33:25,680
is blinding me.

550
00:33:27,559 --> 00:33:28,160
By the way,

551
00:33:28,359 --> 00:33:29,400
how's Zhou Jun's case going?

552
00:33:31,160 --> 00:33:32,200
It's proceeding normally.

553
00:33:32,480 --> 00:33:33,039
Zhou Jun's parents
have already been to the law firm.

554
00:33:34,960 --> 00:33:36,119
Originally, they wanted to hire you

555
00:33:36,119 --> 00:33:37,079
to take the case.

556
00:33:37,240 --> 00:33:38,279
But I explained

557
00:33:38,799 --> 00:33:39,839
your situation to them,

558
00:33:40,559 --> 00:33:41,440
and then they agreed

559
00:33:41,440 --> 00:33:42,480
to let Ms. Zhang take it.

560
00:33:43,799 --> 00:33:44,400
Where is Ms. Zhang?

561
00:33:58,680 --> 00:33:59,720
Where is Xu Huaisong?

562
00:34:00,839 --> 00:34:01,759
Why didn't he come?

563
00:34:02,319 --> 00:34:03,319
I'm Lawyer Zhang Ling
from Zhikun Law Firm.

564
00:34:04,759 --> 00:34:06,319
Your family has entrusted me

565
00:34:06,400 --> 00:34:07,960
to act as your defense counsel in your case

566
00:34:08,119 --> 00:34:09,519
involving suspected intentional homicide and kidnapping.

567
00:34:10,360 --> 00:34:11,480
Do you have any objection?

568
00:34:17,400 --> 00:34:18,159
I do.

569
00:34:18,159 --> 00:34:19,480
I only want Xu Huaisong.

570
00:34:19,760 --> 00:34:21,159
I said I only want Xu Huaisong.

571
00:34:21,159 --> 00:34:22,239
Only he can save me.

572
00:34:22,239 --> 00:34:23,039
I told you that
before this!

573
00:34:23,760 --> 00:34:24,920
Xu Huaisong!

574
00:34:25,559 --> 00:34:26,280
Mr. Xu does not have

575
00:34:26,280 --> 00:34:27,400
a domestic law license.

576
00:34:28,400 --> 00:34:29,719
He can neither defend you

577
00:34:30,360 --> 00:34:31,440
nor appear in court for you.

578
00:34:33,119 --> 00:34:33,760
Whether you reject me or not,
you have no choice

579
00:34:35,280 --> 00:34:36,559
but to trust me.

580
00:34:47,280 --> 00:34:47,960
Fine.

581
00:34:51,639 --> 00:34:52,599
About this case.

582
00:34:52,599 --> 00:34:53,960
Tell me exactly

583
00:34:54,079 --> 00:34:55,119
how you stated the facts

584
00:34:55,119 --> 00:34:55,800
to the police.

585
00:35:09,519 --> 00:35:10,559
Is it kind of inappropriate

586
00:35:10,559 --> 00:35:11,480
for me to be here?

587
00:35:11,760 --> 00:35:12,599
Could there be
privacy concerns?

588
00:35:13,880 --> 00:35:15,440
You know both the victim

589
00:35:15,440 --> 00:35:16,519
and the suspect.

590
00:35:16,920 --> 00:35:18,280
Maybe you can provide us

591
00:35:18,280 --> 00:35:19,400
with some useful information.

592
00:35:19,719 --> 00:35:20,719
Just sit in and listen.

593
00:35:21,159 --> 00:35:21,679
Okay.

594
00:35:24,639 --> 00:35:26,639
This is the material I organized

595
00:35:26,639 --> 00:35:27,639
after speaking with Zhou Jun.
Take a look.

596
00:35:32,960 --> 00:35:34,599
According to Zhou Jun,

597
00:35:34,639 --> 00:35:36,039
when the victim was killed,

598
00:35:36,119 --> 00:35:37,599
he himself was not at the scene.

599
00:35:37,760 --> 00:35:38,639
On the day of the incident,

600
00:35:38,639 --> 00:35:39,760
the victim was driving.

601
00:35:40,239 --> 00:35:42,039
About forty minutes before the crime,

602
00:35:42,519 --> 00:35:44,079
Zhou Jun was in the passenger seat

603
00:35:44,280 --> 00:35:46,400
and had a conflict with the victim.

604
00:35:46,800 --> 00:35:47,639
What caused it?

605
00:35:48,199 --> 00:35:49,199
Zhou Jun said after the victim

606
00:35:49,199 --> 00:35:50,639
started working at Huan Vision,

607
00:35:50,639 --> 00:35:51,719
She was always working late and socializing.

608
00:35:51,719 --> 00:35:53,320
They had less and less time together.

609
00:35:53,880 --> 00:35:55,360
And when she was with him,

610
00:35:55,360 --> 00:35:56,400
she was often distracted.

611
00:35:56,599 --> 00:35:57,920
So for a while, he suspected

612
00:35:57,920 --> 00:35:59,400
she was cheating on him.

613
00:36:00,280 --> 00:36:01,280
They argued more than once
over this.

614
00:36:04,800 --> 00:36:06,159
Have you ever seen them quarrel?

615
00:36:07,480 --> 00:36:07,960
Yes.

616
00:36:08,519 --> 00:36:09,920
I remember last month,

617
00:36:10,199 --> 00:36:11,599
the day Huaisong flew to America.

618
00:36:15,719 --> 00:36:16,559
Stay safe.
We're heading off first.

619
00:36:18,599 --> 00:36:19,239
Bye.

620
00:36:20,360 --> 00:36:20,920
Bye.

621
00:36:30,360 --> 00:36:31,639
Why are you still mad at me?

622
00:36:35,840 --> 00:36:37,280
Other than that time, were there more?

623
00:36:38,199 --> 00:36:39,199
A few more times.

624
00:36:39,360 --> 00:36:40,719
All downstairs at Huan Vision.

625
00:36:42,760 --> 00:36:43,599
And...

626
00:36:43,840 --> 00:36:45,519
Yao Xin's attitude toward Zhou Jun

627
00:36:45,880 --> 00:36:47,440
really had been pretty cold all along.

628
00:36:48,000 --> 00:36:49,320
I'll check the ride- hailing records

629
00:36:49,320 --> 00:36:50,840
on my phone for exact dates

630
00:36:50,920 --> 00:36:51,880
and send you screenshots later.

631
00:36:52,639 --> 00:36:53,199
Okay.

632
00:36:54,360 --> 00:36:55,360
About his suspicion that the victim
was cheating,

633
00:36:56,599 --> 00:36:58,039
did Zhou Jun have any solid evidence?

634
00:36:58,119 --> 00:36:58,880
No.

635
00:36:59,840 --> 00:37:01,079
Zhou Jun said on the day of the crime,

636
00:37:01,079 --> 00:37:02,880
he wanted to check her phone

637
00:37:02,880 --> 00:37:04,119
to confirm whether she was cheating,

638
00:37:04,119 --> 00:37:05,480
but she stopped him.

639
00:37:05,559 --> 00:37:06,400
They argued,

640
00:37:06,400 --> 00:37:07,559
then got physical.

641
00:37:08,199 --> 00:37:09,079
The victim scratched
Zhou Jun's arm.

642
00:37:10,400 --> 00:37:11,920
One key piece of evidence the police have

643
00:37:11,920 --> 00:37:13,679
against Zhou Jun is that

644
00:37:14,679 --> 00:37:15,960
tissue found

645
00:37:15,960 --> 00:37:17,119
under the victim's nails

646
00:37:17,519 --> 00:37:18,360
matches
Zhou Jun's DNA.

647
00:37:20,400 --> 00:37:21,639
But Zhou Jun says

648
00:37:21,719 --> 00:37:22,519
after the physical fight,
he got out of the car.

649
00:37:23,920 --> 00:37:25,440
The victim drove away alone.

650
00:37:25,559 --> 00:37:26,400
He wandered by himself
on the mountain road

651
00:37:27,159 --> 00:37:28,239
for a while.

652
00:37:28,559 --> 00:37:29,760
There was nowhere nearby,

653
00:37:30,000 --> 00:37:31,079
and his phone had died,

654
00:37:31,079 --> 00:37:32,719
so he walked to the teacher's house.

655
00:37:33,079 --> 00:37:34,239
After that, he had dinner

656
00:37:34,239 --> 00:37:35,039
with the teacher,
and then received

657
00:37:35,800 --> 00:37:37,119
the news that the victim had been killed.

658
00:37:38,039 --> 00:37:39,159
So at present, has there been

659
00:37:39,239 --> 00:37:40,719
no second suspect in this case?

660
00:37:41,360 --> 00:37:42,039
Not for now.

661
00:37:42,599 --> 00:37:43,360
There's no surveillance
on that mountain road,

662
00:37:44,400 --> 00:37:45,239
and there was no dashcam

663
00:37:45,239 --> 00:37:46,599
in the victim's car either.

664
00:37:47,239 --> 00:37:49,119
No biological traces other than Zhou Jun's

665
00:37:49,119 --> 00:37:50,360
and the victim's were found in the car,

666
00:37:50,360 --> 00:37:51,280
including on the murder weapon,

667
00:37:51,559 --> 00:37:52,840
the claw hammer.

668
00:37:54,239 --> 00:37:55,440
As for the crime scene,

669
00:37:56,239 --> 00:37:56,880
because it happened

670
00:37:56,880 --> 00:37:58,280
to pour that day,

671
00:37:58,280 --> 00:37:59,400
many traces were destroyed.

672
00:38:00,000 --> 00:38:01,239
Collecting evidence has been difficult.

673
00:38:01,840 --> 00:38:03,519
The police are still investigating further.

674
00:38:15,639 --> 00:38:16,599
Say what you want to say.

675
00:38:19,440 --> 00:38:20,079
Mr. Xu.

676
00:38:20,400 --> 00:38:21,679
judging from things so far,

677
00:38:21,679 --> 00:38:23,079
this case doesn't look very promising.

678
00:38:23,400 --> 00:38:24,599
I know you don't have

679
00:38:24,599 --> 00:38:25,559
a domestic law license,

680
00:38:25,760 --> 00:38:27,719
but for some difficult cases

681
00:38:27,719 --> 00:38:28,920
at Zhikun Law Firm,

682
00:38:29,079 --> 00:38:30,280
you sometimes do get involved.

683
00:38:33,679 --> 00:38:34,719
For Zhou Jun's case,

684
00:38:35,320 --> 00:38:36,119
do you want to join us?

685
00:38:39,119 --> 00:38:39,760
Ms. Zhang,

686
00:38:40,360 --> 00:38:42,000
Mr. Xu isn't that familiar

687
00:38:42,000 --> 00:38:42,920
with criminal cases either.

688
00:38:42,920 --> 00:38:44,159
I think we should leave him out this time.

689
00:38:45,039 --> 00:38:45,679
The questions
Mr. Xu just asked

690
00:38:46,480 --> 00:38:47,360
were all right on point.

691
00:38:47,360 --> 00:38:48,760
He sounded very professional.

692
00:38:50,360 --> 00:38:52,920
Not like someone unfamiliar with it.

693
00:38:56,280 --> 00:38:56,760
Listen.

694
00:38:57,280 --> 00:38:58,079
you keep handling
Zhou Jun's case as usual.

695
00:38:59,719 --> 00:39:01,039
As for whether I get involved,

696
00:39:01,599 --> 00:39:02,239
we'll discuss it later.

697
00:39:10,320 --> 00:39:11,519
I thought you'd try to persuade me,

698
00:39:12,239 --> 00:39:13,079
or at least ask

699
00:39:13,199 --> 00:39:14,679
why I don't take criminal cases.

700
00:39:16,320 --> 00:39:17,199
Everyone has secrets
in their heart.

701
00:39:18,880 --> 00:39:20,400
If you don't want to take criminal cases,

702
00:39:20,800 --> 00:39:22,199
then you must have your reasons.

703
00:39:23,280 --> 00:39:24,519
And if there's a reason you don't want to say,

704
00:39:25,039 --> 00:39:25,880
then you must have

705
00:39:26,159 --> 00:39:27,199
your reason for that too.

706
00:39:30,360 --> 00:39:31,440
But if you want to talk,

707
00:39:32,239 --> 00:39:33,119
I'll always be here.

708
00:39:37,079 --> 00:39:38,360
I was upstairs in a meeting just now.

709
00:39:38,559 --> 00:39:39,480
You waited long, didn't you?

710
00:39:40,039 --> 00:39:40,679
I just got here.

711
00:39:41,679 --> 00:39:43,320
I specially packed some good food for you.

712
00:39:48,559 --> 00:39:49,239
Mingying?

713
00:39:49,760 --> 00:39:50,400
You're that sweet?

714
00:39:50,800 --> 00:39:51,559
Hug me.

715
00:39:54,159 --> 00:39:55,000
What's wrong?

716
00:39:55,480 --> 00:39:56,840
Xu Huaisong and Ruan Yu are right behind us.

717
00:39:58,400 --> 00:39:59,159
Don't turn around.

718
00:40:02,840 --> 00:40:03,400
Liu Mao?

719
00:40:11,760 --> 00:40:12,480
What do we do?

720
00:40:13,880 --> 00:40:16,199
Maybe we should t- tell the truth?

721
00:40:16,559 --> 00:40:17,679
Shut up. They're coming over.

722
00:40:23,840 --> 00:40:24,559
Mingying.

723
00:40:27,000 --> 00:40:27,559
What a coincidence.

724
00:40:27,559 --> 00:40:28,679
I was just calling you.

725
00:40:29,719 --> 00:40:30,480
Why are you here?

726
00:40:30,840 --> 00:40:34,000
I brought you food.

727
00:40:34,119 --> 00:40:35,079
It's all your favorites.

728
00:40:35,559 --> 00:40:37,119
That was originally mine!

729
00:40:38,440 --> 00:40:39,880
You're the best.

730
00:40:40,199 --> 00:40:42,079
This one was originally mine too!

731
00:40:42,760 --> 00:40:44,039
You said you were going downstairs to eat.

732
00:40:47,880 --> 00:40:49,159
You said you were going downstairs for food.

733
00:40:49,480 --> 00:40:50,280
Why are you here?

734
00:40:52,519 --> 00:40:53,000
Food?

735
00:40:53,639 --> 00:40:54,239
Yeah.

736
00:40:55,440 --> 00:40:56,199
I- I- I...
I just came downstairs to eat,

737
00:40:57,320 --> 00:40:58,360
and then I ran into Ming...

738
00:41:00,440 --> 00:41:01,400
ran into Miss Shen.

739
00:41:03,960 --> 00:41:05,559
Since we happened to run into each other,

740
00:41:05,760 --> 00:41:06,719
why don't we eat together?

741
00:41:09,360 --> 00:41:10,079
No, no, no.
You two eat.

742
00:41:11,679 --> 00:41:12,639
It doesn't matter.

743
00:41:12,880 --> 00:41:14,159
All four of us know each other anyway.

744
00:41:15,239 --> 00:41:16,000
Let's eat together.

745
00:41:18,480 --> 00:41:19,320
Together.

746
00:41:21,280 --> 00:41:21,960
Let's go.

747
00:41:33,000 --> 00:41:34,239
Think of it as extra food for me.

748
00:41:34,480 --> 00:41:35,079
Eat more.
Let me see

749
00:41:35,679 --> 00:41:36,840
what yummy food you brought me.

750
00:41:37,679 --> 00:41:38,960
- I ordered that.
- Please. Longjing shrimp.

751
00:41:42,639 --> 00:41:43,480
What a coincidence.

752
00:41:43,960 --> 00:41:45,119
This is Longjing shrimp too.

753
00:41:47,400 --> 00:41:48,239
The extra food is too.

754
00:41:48,519 --> 00:41:49,719
Such a coincidence.

755
00:41:51,280 --> 00:41:52,159
Sure is.

756
00:41:52,519 --> 00:41:53,920
That's what happens when you're blessed.

757
00:41:54,039 --> 00:41:54,880
Good food just keeps coming

758
00:41:55,000 --> 00:41:56,079
when you want.

759
00:41:56,360 --> 00:41:56,960
Right?

760
00:41:57,280 --> 00:41:58,480
Hello, spicy diced chicken.

761
00:41:58,760 --> 00:41:59,599
Enjoy. Thank you.

762
00:42:01,119 --> 00:42:01,760
See?

763
00:42:01,760 --> 00:42:03,039
This one I don't like.

764
00:42:03,039 --> 00:42:03,960
I don't eat spicy food.

765
00:42:04,800 --> 00:42:05,840
Among spicy dishes,

766
00:42:05,840 --> 00:42:07,079
there's only one I like.

767
00:42:07,159 --> 00:42:07,920
Know what it is?
Mapo tofu?

768
00:42:08,960 --> 00:42:10,119
It is mapo tofu.

769
00:42:16,719 --> 00:42:17,639
Mapo tofu.

770
00:42:18,559 --> 00:42:20,400
You forgot? I like that too.

771
00:42:21,079 --> 00:42:21,679
I'd prepared
a meal for two today.

772
00:42:22,639 --> 00:42:23,719
I wanted us to eat it together.

773
00:42:23,760 --> 00:42:24,920
I remember back in college,

774
00:42:24,920 --> 00:42:25,960
mapo tofu was your favorite.

775
00:42:25,960 --> 00:42:27,199
Right, from that place outside school.

776
00:42:27,519 --> 00:42:28,440
Yeah, that one.
You still remember?

777
00:42:36,159 --> 00:42:37,800
[Talk less!]

778
00:42:50,280 --> 00:42:51,119
Your phone rang.

779
00:42:56,079 --> 00:42:57,039
I'll reply to a message.

780
00:42:58,159 --> 00:42:58,800
Go ahead.

781
00:42:59,760 --> 00:43:00,639
Mr. Liu.

782
00:43:01,280 --> 00:43:02,559
you usually don't keep

783
00:43:02,559 --> 00:43:03,800
your phone on silent?

784
00:43:06,320 --> 00:43:08,239
Normally, I'm afraid

785
00:43:08,639 --> 00:43:09,960
of missing

786
00:43:09,960 --> 00:43:11,519
important case updates.

787
00:43:11,519 --> 00:43:12,079
I'm used to it.

788
00:43:12,079 --> 00:43:13,360
So I habitually

789
00:43:13,719 --> 00:43:14,760
keep the volume high.

790
00:43:15,559 --> 00:43:16,639
Then look at it.

791
00:43:19,239 --> 00:43:19,920
I am looking.

792
00:43:21,039 --> 00:43:21,800
Take it out.

793
00:43:22,519 --> 00:43:23,440
Of course I'll look.

794
00:43:33,400 --> 00:43:35,000
Hello, sweet- and- sour ribs. Enjoy.

795
00:43:36,119 --> 00:43:37,480
It's a news push.

796
00:43:39,599 --> 00:43:41,320
This is my favorite dish.

797
00:43:41,840 --> 00:43:42,960
Did you prepare it for me?

798
00:43:43,239 --> 00:43:44,000
Look.

799
00:43:46,760 --> 00:43:47,559
Shen Mingying.

800
00:43:51,119 --> 00:43:53,039
No way. Look at this.

801
00:43:54,440 --> 00:43:55,320
What did I say?

802
00:43:55,920 --> 00:43:57,159
Your favorite has to be included.

803
00:43:58,920 --> 00:43:59,639
Come on, eat.

804
00:44:00,000 --> 00:44:00,880
That's more like it.

805
00:44:17,920 --> 00:44:19,480
Seriously,

806
00:44:20,239 --> 00:44:21,480
you people in relationships,

807
00:44:21,480 --> 00:44:23,239
can't you spare a thought

808
00:44:23,239 --> 00:44:23,920
for us

809
00:44:23,920 --> 00:44:25,400
single folks?

810
00:44:25,400 --> 00:44:25,960
Right?

811
00:44:26,239 --> 00:44:27,280
You're overflowing with love,

812
00:44:27,280 --> 00:44:28,119
and we...

813
00:44:29,119 --> 00:44:30,039
we...

814
00:44:30,239 --> 00:44:31,480
we'll just huddle together for warmth.

815
00:44:31,719 --> 00:44:33,480
Right. Then serve me some,

816
00:44:34,000 --> 00:44:34,639
and I'll serve you some too.

817
00:44:34,639 --> 00:44:35,719
Sure, sure, okay.

818
00:44:36,400 --> 00:44:37,039
- Come on, come on.
- Thanks, thanks.
Eat more.

819
00:44:37,639 --> 00:44:38,599
One bite each. Eat more.
Okay, thanks.

820
00:44:39,239 --> 00:44:40,039
What else do you want?

821
00:44:40,360 --> 00:44:41,079
You two are doing pretty well
with your little huddle.

822
00:44:42,400 --> 00:44:43,559
Have you eaten together before?

823
00:44:43,599 --> 00:44:44,400
- Yes.
- No.

824
00:44:51,159 --> 00:44:53,679
Before, Mr. Liu helped me handle

825
00:44:53,679 --> 00:44:55,199
that breakup dispute.

826
00:44:55,360 --> 00:44:56,519
So to thank him,

827
00:44:56,519 --> 00:44:57,960
I treated him to one meal.

828
00:44:58,360 --> 00:44:59,239
Just that once.

829
00:44:59,280 --> 00:45:00,480
I forgot about it.

830
00:45:02,360 --> 00:45:03,920
Yeah, just once.

831
00:45:04,159 --> 00:45:04,880
Just once.

832
00:45:07,400 --> 00:45:08,360
Just once.

833
00:45:20,400 --> 00:45:21,159
Have some shrimp.
Shrimp is good.

834
00:45:24,679 --> 00:45:25,960
Your cooking has improved lately.

835
00:45:25,960 --> 00:45:26,679
Yeah.

836
00:45:26,719 --> 00:45:27,960
It made me think again

837
00:45:28,280 --> 00:45:29,440
of my father's case back then.

838
00:45:35,719 --> 00:45:36,559
That's it for now.

839
00:45:37,159 --> 00:45:38,760
Y- You two go ahead.

840
00:45:40,519 --> 00:45:42,280
I- I- I'll keep warming myself up.

841
00:45:42,280 --> 00:45:43,000
Warm myself to the end.

842
00:45:43,400 --> 00:45:44,360
I- I'll drive you home.

843
00:45:46,320 --> 00:45:47,559
No need. I'll just get a cab.

844
00:45:47,679 --> 00:45:49,639
Come on, see it through to the end.

845
00:45:51,280 --> 00:45:51,880
Right?
Right.

846
00:45:53,599 --> 00:45:56,159
Okay then, thanks, Mr. Liu.

847
00:45:56,440 --> 00:45:57,079
Don't mention it.
Let's go.

848
00:45:58,159 --> 00:45:58,960
We're heading off then.

849
00:45:59,480 --> 00:46:00,000
Go on.
Bye- bye.

850
00:46:01,679 --> 00:46:02,400
Go on now.

851
00:46:13,239 --> 00:46:14,559
Mr. Xu probably isn't coming.

852
00:46:15,000 --> 00:46:16,079
Let's start discussing.

853
00:46:16,079 --> 00:46:17,480
Okay, let's begin.

854
00:46:48,360 --> 00:46:48,960
Actually, back then,

855
00:46:48,960 --> 00:46:50,199
I didn't really understand my dad.

856
00:46:51,360 --> 00:46:52,559
The suspect

857
00:46:53,119 --> 00:46:54,440
had already been arrested.

858
00:46:54,800 --> 00:46:55,840
The charge was filed too.

859
00:46:59,320 --> 00:47:00,280
By defending him,

860
00:47:00,280 --> 00:47:01,679
you were exploiting a loophole in the law!

861
00:47:01,679 --> 00:47:03,000
That's not a loophole in the law!

862
00:47:03,400 --> 00:47:04,639
That's a legal principle.

863
00:47:05,760 --> 00:47:06,880
You're not a criminal defense lawyer.

864
00:47:07,480 --> 00:47:08,400
You don't understand the meaning
of criminal defense at all.

865
00:47:11,280 --> 00:47:12,000
So,

866
00:47:12,639 --> 00:47:14,119
you chose to become a criminal defense lawyer

867
00:47:15,320 --> 00:47:16,320
to find the meaning

868
00:47:16,320 --> 00:47:17,559
Uncle talked about?

869
00:47:20,920 --> 00:47:21,840
To be exact,

870
00:47:22,920 --> 00:47:23,599
it was to prove

871
00:47:23,599 --> 00:47:25,000
that the "meaning" he talked about

872
00:47:25,639 --> 00:47:26,639
didn't exist at all.

873
00:47:27,639 --> 00:47:28,480
But in the end,

874
00:47:31,639 --> 00:47:32,519
I found it.

875
00:47:34,159 --> 00:47:35,000
Then later,

876
00:47:36,199 --> 00:47:36,960
why not
taking criminal cases?

877
00:47:40,840 --> 00:47:42,159
Back then, I worked with my father

878
00:47:42,679 --> 00:47:43,960
on a criminal case.

879
00:47:44,920 --> 00:47:46,039
It was also a murder case.

880
00:47:46,320 --> 00:47:47,199
In that case,

881
00:47:47,480 --> 00:47:48,800
all I was doing was trying my utmost

882
00:47:48,800 --> 00:47:49,639
to protect my client's
lawful rights.

883
00:47:54,000 --> 00:47:55,039
Search your heart.

884
00:47:55,679 --> 00:47:57,320
Were you really never shaken even a little?

885
00:48:00,760 --> 00:48:02,119
Since you were shaken,

886
00:48:03,440 --> 00:48:04,559
then you're not qualified

887
00:48:04,960 --> 00:48:06,400
to stand in court for your client.

888
00:48:07,519 --> 00:48:08,360
You are not fit

889
00:48:09,480 --> 00:48:10,639
to be a criminal defense lawyer.

890
00:48:15,840 --> 00:48:16,599
I admit it.

891
00:48:18,079 --> 00:48:18,880
I was shaken.

892
00:48:20,840 --> 00:48:22,360
So I withdrew from that case.

893
00:48:25,679 --> 00:48:26,440
Later on,

894
00:48:27,000 --> 00:48:27,519
after I'd built up

895
00:48:27,519 --> 00:48:28,760
a lot of experience,

896
00:48:29,760 --> 00:48:31,000
when I wanted to try again and become

897
00:48:31,000 --> 00:48:32,480
a qualified criminal lawyer,

898
00:48:36,039 --> 00:48:37,159
my father suddenly had a stroke.

899
00:48:40,800 --> 00:48:42,039
And when he woke up,

900
00:48:44,360 --> 00:48:45,519
he remembered nothing.

901
00:48:50,159 --> 00:48:51,480
So the conclusion he left behind

902
00:48:51,760 --> 00:48:53,159
while he was still lucid

903
00:48:54,360 --> 00:48:55,199
somehow became the one judgment

904
00:48:55,199 --> 00:48:56,760
I had no choice but to believe.

905
00:48:59,280 --> 00:49:00,000
Maybe...

906
00:49:01,679 --> 00:49:03,239
maybe I really am not fit to be

907
00:49:03,400 --> 00:49:04,360
a criminal defense lawyer.

908
00:49:04,880 --> 00:49:05,760
That's not true.

909
00:49:06,320 --> 00:49:07,119
I don't believe

910
00:49:07,400 --> 00:49:08,480
every criminal lawyer

911
00:49:08,719 --> 00:49:09,400
goes from start to finish

912
00:49:09,400 --> 00:49:10,559
without ever wavering once.

913
00:49:11,159 --> 00:49:12,840
Some people

914
00:49:13,159 --> 00:49:13,760
give up midway.

915
00:49:14,880 --> 00:49:16,239
Some people hold on.

916
00:49:19,079 --> 00:49:20,519
How could Uncle be so sure

917
00:49:21,639 --> 00:49:22,599
that you wouldn't be one

918
00:49:22,599 --> 00:49:23,800
who holds on to the end?

919
00:49:27,679 --> 00:49:28,599
Whether I am or not,

920
00:49:30,719 --> 00:49:31,360
I'll never get the chance

921
00:49:31,360 --> 00:49:32,400
to prove it to him again.

922
00:49:34,039 --> 00:49:35,360
Then prove it to yourself.

923
00:49:36,360 --> 00:49:37,480
Prove it to your mother.

924
00:49:39,280 --> 00:49:40,360
I once saw

925
00:49:40,599 --> 00:49:41,639
a line online:

926
00:49:43,079 --> 00:49:44,320
"Unfinished lessons

927
00:49:45,280 --> 00:49:47,000
will keep reappearing in your life

928
00:49:47,920 --> 00:49:49,159
until you give a new response."

929
00:49:51,360 --> 00:49:52,639
While studying law,

930
00:49:53,599 --> 00:49:55,119
you came to understand Uncle's defense back then.

931
00:49:56,519 --> 00:49:57,760
But Auntie isn't a lawyer.

932
00:49:58,400 --> 00:49:59,679
She's still trapped in what happened then.

933
00:49:59,679 --> 00:50:00,480
She can't move on.

934
00:50:01,039 --> 00:50:02,360
Uncle no longer has the chance

935
00:50:02,599 --> 00:50:03,639
to speak to her again.

936
00:50:04,199 --> 00:50:05,199
In this family,

937
00:50:06,880 --> 00:50:08,119
the only person to give that response

938
00:50:08,199 --> 00:50:09,159
and help her let go

939
00:50:10,920 --> 00:50:12,000
is you.
